<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by By-Tor:
[B]I guess I'll use your logic:

"Nature's Touch heals 2.2 damage/mana (idtentical to chloroblast.) Less healing per mana than cleric's level 34 superior heal. So your typical 60 druid can heal < 10k off a 4k manabar."

Druids 978 (400 mana, 5.5 sec) 2.445 hp/mana 177 hp/sec (not taking any Class bonuses into consideration)

Cleric 910 (350 mana, 4.5 sec) 2.6 hp/mana 202 hp/sec 

"Druid nukes can't be upgraded, they're already as efficient as wizards, many druids still think of themselves as a healer class for some reason, probably because they're forced into it because of lack of clerics. Some druids want DOT upgrades but since DOTs have no place in groups, and little in raids, it really does nothing to address the class's prime problem."

So you are saying that druids' nukes are the best now (or tied with wizards for #1)?  Wana know why there is a lack of clerics (so you say) cause people would rather play druids....

"Or 1 cleric (for intermediate healing). Which many see as the exact reason why raids will have so many clerics and so few druid/shaman."

Wrong.  Druids can heal just as well as clerics for intermediate healing.  Clerics use Devine Light, druids us Natures Touch...not much different.

Clerics heal and give hitpoints and some AC and res...thats it.  Druids bring so much more to the table.  Quit complaining.  Maybe clerics need to start posting on druid boards about lack of travel.  

We cant port to more that one spot, druids can.
We cant port others, druids can.
We cant increase our speed, druids can.
We cant increase others speed, druids can.
We cant levitate, druids can.
We cant water breathe, druids can.
We cant invis (normal) ourselves, druids can.
We cant invis others (normal), druids can.
etc[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
